This paper deals with optimization methods for training deep neural networks, which is a core problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of Hessian matrices, which are commonly used in numerical analysis and optimization, suggesting that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a likely category as well. The paper also mentions computer vision (cs.CV) as an application area for deep learning, and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a broader field of study. Finally, the paper deals with optimization methods, which is a topic in computer science (cs.DS).
